  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Project Executive",
  "description": "<h3>About the Company</h3><p>Studio Mojo is a multidisciplinary studio comprising consultants and designers with solid track records. We’ve carved a niche in spatial design and execution, creating transformative 360-experiences across galleries, commercial interiors, immersive content, and exhibitions.</p><h3>About the Role</h3><p>As a <strong>Senior Project Executive</strong>, you will support and learn from senior team members while taking responsibility for parts of project delivery. With at least 3–4 years of relevant experience, you’ll bring a working knowledge of design or build projects and the drive to grow into a full project management role.</p><h3>Responsibilities</h3><ul><li>Assist in managing timelines, budgets, and deliverables across multiple projects.</li><li>Coordinate with suppliers, contractors, and vendors to support smooth execution.</li><li>Contribute to the preparation of project proposals, pitches, and presentations.</li><li>Maintain responsive and professional communication with clients and team members.</li><li>Prepare and maintain project documentation such as meeting notes, photo records, and feedback forms.</li><li>Support adoption of Studio Mojo’s processes and tools (e.g., Project Management tools and AI applications).</li><li>Take initiative to improve workflow, client service, and team efficiency.</li></ul><h3>Qualifications</h3><ul><li>Diploma in Architecture, Interior Design, Project Management, or related field.</li><li>3–4 years of relevant experience in design, build, events, or creative industries.</li><li>Basic understanding of project workflows, budgeting, and supplier coordination.</li><li>Strong organizational and multitasking skills with attention to detail.</li><li>Effective communication skills in both client-facing and team settings.</li><li>Eagerness to learn, adapt, and take on increasing responsibility over time.</li><li>Familiarity with project management or design software is an advantage.</li></ul>",
